  "body": "# Problem\n\nFrom Trail of Bits:\n\n> There is a configuration for a debug keystore, but not for a production keystore. Ensure that you aren't running the application in a debug configuration at all times. \n\n> Similar to the iOS version of the application, excessive permissions are being set for the application. Does it actually require NFC access? There is even a line in the android manifest saying: \n\n <!-- these permissions should be removed -->\n\n    <!-- React Native unnecessary permissions (https://github.com/facebook/react-native/issues/5886) -->\n\n    <uses-permission android:name=\"android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE\" tools:node=\"remove\"/>\n\n## Notes\n\nAs with[ iOS](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/8282), we need to go through the Android permissions and remove anything unnecessary.",
