    "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nLooking at the list of permissions in the Android manifest (https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml) and after installing the Android app and playing with it a bit - It looks like the following permissions can be removed without affecting the app's functionality:\r\n1. android.permission.NFC - can be removed assuming there is not NFC functionality (transferring funds from one device in proximity to another)\r\n2. android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION - can be removed assuming the app doesn't use the device's location services.\r\n3. android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE - This permission enables the app to access the device's mobile info (cellular network info, phone number, call log, text messages etc). I cannot think of a reason for Status to need this permission.\r\n\r\nThere are additional permissions i the manifest that might be redundant as well but I haven't had the time to dig into it. the ones I listed are the major ones.",
